#ROOM
Vnum     30040
Name     &bBlackfathom Deeps - The Sunken Entry&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The air is freezing and smells of salt and decay. Ancient night elf 
statues, worn smooth by centuries of tides, lean precariously against 
the damp walls. A swirling, deep-blue portal blocks the path forward, 
separating the caverns of Ashenvale from the corrupted temple below.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    28040
Desc      Return to the surface of Zoram Strand.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30041
Desc      Enter the submerged tunnels.~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30041
Name     &bSubmerged Tunnel - South&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The floor is covered in a foot of murky water. Small, eyeless fish 
dart away from your light, and the walls are thick with bioluminescent 
algae that provides a dim, sickly green glow.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30040
Desc      The entrance portal.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30042
Desc      The tunnel opens into a large pool.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30001 10 30041
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30042
Name     &bThe Pool of Ask'ar&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This massive natural cavern is half-filled with sea water. Stone 
platforms rise from the depths, connected by crumbling bridges. The 
sound of rhythmic gurgling suggests a large murloc presence.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30041
Desc      The entry tunnel.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30046
Desc      The path toward the turtle's lair.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    30043
Desc      A small side alcove.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    30044
Desc      A small side alcove.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30001 10 30042
Reset O 0 30039 5 30042
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30043
Name     &bMurloc Alcove - East&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A cramped, damp corner of the pool. Piles of fish bones and 
shattered shells suggest this is a feeding ground for the 
local murlocs.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    30042
Desc      Return to the pool.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 30009 10 30043
Reset O 0 30032 5 30043
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30044
Name     &bMurloc Alcove - West&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The water is deeper here. The walls are covered in crude murloc 
paintings made of crushed coral and squid ink.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    30042
Desc      Return to the pool.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30001 10 30044
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30045
Name     &bThe Flooded Passage&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The path narrows as it dives beneath a low-hanging rock arch. 
You must wade through chest-deep water to proceed.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30042
Desc      The Pool of Ask'ar.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30046
Desc      Ghamoo-ra's Chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30003 10 30045
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30046
Name     &bChamber of the Ancient Snapjaw&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This cavern is dominated by a single, massive stone platform 
surrounded by deep water. Ghamoo-ra, a turtle of legendary size, 
rests here, his shell looking like an island in the gloom.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30045
Desc      The flooded passage.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30047
Desc      The naga hallways.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30010 1 30046
  Reset G 1 30022 1
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30047
Name     &cNaga Hallway - Entrance&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The architecture here shifts from natural cavern to elven ruins. 
Blue silk banners hang from the walls, and the floor is made of 
finely polished marble, though it is slick with sea-slime.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30046
Desc      Ghamoo-ra's Chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30048
Desc      The hallway continues.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30000 10 30047
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30048
Name     &cNaga Hallway - Central&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The hallway is wider here. To the east and west, high-arched 
doorways lead to barracks where the naga warriors rest between 
patrols.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30050
Desc      Lady Sarevess's Sanctum.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30047
Desc      The hallway entry.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    30049
Desc      Naga Barracks.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30000 10 30048
Reset O 0 30038 10 30048
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30049
Name     &cNaga Barracks&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Piles of dried kelp serve as beds. Tridents and shields are 
leaned against the walls, ready for a quick defense.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    30048
Desc      Return to the hallway.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 30000 10 30049
Reset O 0 30036 10 30049
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     30050
Name     &cLady Sarevess's Sanctum&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The room is bone-chillingly cold. Lady Sarevess stands at the 
far end of the hall, her icy gaze fixed on the entrance. The 
marble floor is covered in a thin layer of frost.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    30048
Desc      The naga hallway.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    30051
Desc      The Moonshrine Ruins.~
